It is true, right now, one needs to be aware of missing values in the application logic. I personally like that, an `Option` makes it very explicit and easy to grasp. Also the byte overhead for the option field is okay, as most fields will not be nullable and not carry this overhead. The serialization logic is also more CPU efficient that way.

What is true is that there is a problem when converting from a `Table` to a `DataSet[Tuple]`. Tables with nullable fields could only be converted to data sets of class types, which would support nullable fields.
